    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1884-08-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1884-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="259" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                <head>No. 258.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Davis</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Morgan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1884-08-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 8,
                            1884</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 629.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I herewith transmit for your files, as
                        promised, in the Department’s instruction to you, No. 609, of the 11th
                        ultimo, a copy of the note<note n="*" xml:id="d259fn1">For inclosure see
                            document No. 265 <hi rend="italic">post.</hi>
                    </note> of Mr. Romero, the
                        minister of Mexico here, of the 12th June, presenting the claim of his
                        Government to certain islands in the Rio Grande, near Roma, Tex.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN DAVIS,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
